                    "description": "For a period of six months, I wrote my MSc thesis in collaboration with Commonland. Within my thesis, I analysed how stakeholders collaborate to blend investments for landscape restoration projects on both project and fund level. The research highlighted the importance of intermediaries such as project developers and fund managers which are crucial in blending investments for landscape restoration. My thesis contributed to the areas of finance for landscape restoration and blended finance, a structuring approach for financing development which theoretically sounds very appealing, but in practice is not widespread yet. \n\nI presented the outcomes of my thesis both to the staff of Commonland as within a webinar hosted by the WWF Landscape Finance Lab. \n\nThe collaboration with Commonland allowed me to get deep insights into the opportunities and barriers for (financing) landscape restoration projects. Commonland provided me with their knowledge, projects, network and enthusiasm for landscape restoration. In turn, I devoted my MSc thesis to a topic relevant to their operations.",
